==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perish
<hw>Per"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Perished</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Perishing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>perissen</ets>, <ets>perisshen</ets>, F. <ets>p⟦eacute⟧rir</ets>,
p. pr. <ets>p⟦eacute⟧rissant</ets>, L. <ets>perire</ets> to go or run
through, come to nothing, perish; <ets>per</ets> through +
<ets>ire</ets> to go. Cf. <er>Issue</er>, and see <er>-ish</er>.]</ety>
<def>To be destroyed; to pass away; to become nothing; to be lost; to
die; hence, to wither; to waste away.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>perish</qex> with hunger!</q> <rj><qau>Luke xv.
17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Grow up and <qex>perish</qex>, as the summer fly.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The thoughts of a soul that <qex>perish</qex> in thinking.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perish</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Perish
<hw>Per"ish</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cause perish.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>perish the thought</b></col> <cd>I hope it will never
happen; -- a phrase used after mention of a possible undesirable event,
sometimes facetiously.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perishability</ent>⟦br⟧
